---
import PublicationLayout from '../layouts/PublicationLayout.astro';
import { SITE_TAGLINE } from '../consts';
---

<PublicationLayout
  title='About'
  description='About the publication, editorial stance, and AI-assisted production approach.'
>
  <section class='about-hero'>
    <p class='kicker'>About the publication</p>
    <h1>Practical reporting on LLM products, AI agents, and the service economy around them.</h1>
    <p class='lead'>{SITE_TAGLINE}</p>
  </section>

  <section class='about-grid'>
    <article class='card panel'>
      <h2>What this publication covers</h2>
      <p>
        Signal & Circuit tracks the people and systems turning large language models into useful work.
        That includes builder tooling, agent workflows, release shifts, managed AI services, and the operational
        realities that appear once products hit daily production use.
      </p>
      <p>
        The audience is two groups at once: developers shipping real products with LLMs, and operators or
        entrepreneurs using AI systems to solve narrow business problems in the field.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class='card panel'>
      <h2>Editorial stance</h2>
      <p>
        This is a practitioner-first publication. No empty hype, no press-release rewriting, and no fake
        certainty where the evidence is thin. If a workflow is messy, expensive, brittle, or only works in
        a sandbox, that matters.
      </p>
      <p>
        We care about what survives contact with real operations: support load, maintenance burden,
        deployment friction, pricing shifts, and whether a system still helps after the novelty wears off.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class='card panel'>
      <h2>How we publish</h2>
      <p>
        Signal & Circuit runs an editorial workflow designed for repeatable quality: topic selection,
        source gathering, draft production, editorial review, and final approval before publication.
      </p>
      <p>
        Automated tooling supports research and first-pass drafting. Editorial judgment controls what ships.
        Every story is reviewed for accuracy, clarity, and practical value before it reaches readers.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class='card panel disclosure'>
      <h2>Disclosure</h2>
      <p>
        Signal & Circuit uses automated research and drafting tools. All articles are editorially reviewed before publication.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you spot an error or have a correction, send it to the editorial team and we will review and update promptly.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</PublicationLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    max-width: 72ch;
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
    color: rgb(var(--muted));
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .panel {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    border-radius: 0;
  }

  .panel p {
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .disclosure {
    background: rgba(var(--surface-strong), 0.7);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
